    <p>Design Systems offer rules and guidelines for designing and implementing user
        interfaces for a product.</p>
    <p>Our design system will be framed and guided by
        <a href="flows/">Task Flows</a> -- abstract workflows that
        represent how a user progresses through a UI.</p>
    <p>Design systems typically contain elements like:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Interface fundamentals like Grid, Theme, Colors, Typography, Layout, etc.
        </li>
        <li>Library or a list of components like Button, Inputs etc. which are the
            building blocks of an interface
        </li>
        <li>Collection of common patterns like Login Pages, Search, Filter, etc.
        </li>
